{{pl/Development/NewGRF/ottdp|0.6|2.6|ttdprev=r1755}} Since TTDPatch r1755, you can use the text reference stack for your error messages, similarly to callback 3A. The only difference is that only 4 registers are copied instead of 6 because error messages support 20 bytes of reference stack only, and two of those bytes may be used by TTD.
